1.	Declare the class and extend react.component. Then set Stuup the constructor, the super and the this.state.

2.	Mounting phase: Render method is invoked and add componentDidMount
Update Phase: Use setState to change state data. Can use shouldComponentUpdate.
Un-Mounting phase: Component is removed from screen. Can use componentWillUnmount

3.	Ok

4.	Logic that is built into a component.

5.	Arrange: Set up code that can be tested.
Act: Call a method that returns a result of our test.
Assert: Expect return to match actual return
